            "draft_value": "* Provides $9 billion for NASA's Science Mission Directorate to restore funding stability and maintain U.S. preeminence over China's expanding space science program.\n* Supports scientific research and STEM workforce training in FL-19, including over $204,000 in cumulative grant funding awarded to Florida Gulf Coast University.\n* Directly impacts the local economy through high-tech contracts, such as those held by local small business Erai, Inc., while delivering a 3:1 national economic return on investment.\n* Funds critical missions identified by the National Academies' Decadal Surveys, ensuring the U.S. continues to set the global norms for 21st-century exploration.",
